HEADWORD: megakaryocyte
<hw>meg`a*kar"y*o*cyte</hw>
<pr>(m⟦ecr⟧g`⟦adot⟧*k⟦acr⟧r"⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*s⟦imac⟧t)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A large bone marrow cell not usually found in
the circulating blood; it is regarded as the precursors of blood
platelets; it is up to 100 ⟦mu⟧m in diameter, with a polyploid nucleus.
Also referred to as <altname>megacaryocyte</altname>,
<altname>megalokaryocyte</altname>, and
<altname>thromboblast</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>megakaryocytic</ent>⟦br⟧
